WorkItem.Description:
Uglify JS has preprocessor capabilities (--define and --define-from-module parameters) allowing to optimize away parts of code based on predefined symbol declarations. For example,
if (typeof DEBUG === "undefined") { DEBUG = true; }
if (DEBUG) {
    console.log(myObj);
}
ran with --define DEBUG=false would've been completely removed from minified version. These capabilities allow having different versions of scripts generated based on symbol values configuration.
It would be great to have a support of such parameters for Uglify JS in .chirp.config files.
